Tanzania’s Energy Regulator Cuts Gasoline Prices by 1.8%, Diesel by 2.3%

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-09-12T04:17:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/tanzania-s-energy-regulator-cuts-gasoline-prices-by-1-8-diesel-by-2-3-.html
Tanzania,  East Africa ’s second-
biggest economy, reduced the price of gasoline by 1.8 percent as
global crude prices declined, the Energy and Water Utilities
Regulatory Authority said.  Gasoline will cost 2,032 Tanzanian shillings ($1.24) per
liter for the next two weeks, the regulator said in a statement
published in the Dar es Salaam-based Guardian newspaper today.  Diesel prices were cut by 2.3 percent to 1,954 shillings
and kerosene, used for cooking, was lowered by the same margin
to 1,934 shillings, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Dar es Salaam at 
 dmalingha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
